<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-22T12:43:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-22T12:43:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.032/25: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-22T17:00:00-00:43"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            22, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Legislature of Liberia adjourned today and not on January 20th as
                                reported Legation’s January 11, 10 a.m.<note n="63" xml:id="d471fn63">Not printed.</note> President of Liberia
                                informs me that Legislature took no action on any applications for
                                concessions.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bundy</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>